--- GRILL-ME SESSION ---

COACH: What problem are you actually solving, and who experiences it?

PARTICIPANT: My SEs spend a considerable amount of time reading, assessing,
researching, populating and preparing for RFPs and their associated demos.
I want to reduce that time and also help them with the demo prep with this
platform. Give a fit score, help populate as much as possible and take it
from there.

COACH recommended one-liner: "Okta Pre-Sales SEs spend 8-40 hours manually
answering RFP security questionnaires and preparing demos. NaughtRFP uses a
multi-agent AI pipeline to auto-answer requirements, score fit/risk, and
generate demo scripts so SEs can focus on the deal."

PARTICIPANT: Yes it does. [confirmed]

---

COACH: What does the 3-minute demo look like? Walk me through exactly what
you would show a judge.

PARTICIPANT: I want to show uploading an RFP which could be a single csv file
or multiple files. Find the questions, question IDs and response tables. Then
assess fit based on Okta service offerings, help answer questions from publicly
available Okta information or from context provided in the response library.
Tell the SE when done analyzing. Have them review human-required responses.
Export in the same file format as ingested. Kick off demo prep and review.

COACH scope recommendation: Must-have: CSV/XLSX upload, agent pipeline, human
review of flagged items, export, demo prep. Nice-to-have/deferred: Google
Sheets/Docs ingestion, email draft, SIG/cert upload as KB sources.

PARTICIPANT: Yes I agree. [scope confirmed]

---

COACH: Where does Okta/identity fit explicitly? This is a judging criterion.

COACH recommendation: Two angles. (1) Content: KB seeded from Okta SIG Core
2024 responses so every AI answer is grounded in what Okta actually offers.
(2) Use case: end users are Okta Pre-Sales SEs; platform directly accelerates
Okta sales motion. The tool IS an identity sales tool.

PARTICIPANT: That is a perfect framing. [confirmed]

---

COACH: Who are the actors using this system?

COACH recommendation: One primary actor - the Okta Pre-Sales SE. Secondary:
SE Manager/team lead via Demo Library.

PARTICIPANT: Okta Pre-Sales SE is the actor. [single actor confirmed]

---

COACH: When should the AI answer confidently vs. hand off to the SE?

COACH recommendation: Flag for human review when confidence below 60%, when
legally sensitive (SLAs, data residency, compliance), or when no KB/web source
backs the answer. Never hallucinate - uncertain = flagged.

PARTICIPANT: Yes that matches well. [confirmed]

---

COACH: What is in the knowledge base and how does it get populated?

COACH recommendation: Three layers: (1) Okta SIG Core 2024 seed ~615 entries,
(2) 25 hand-crafted Okta baseline Q&A, (3) past completed RFPs ingested by SEs
for compounding improvement. Web search fallback to okta.com/trust.okta.com.

PARTICIPANT: The true threshold should be 80-90% although that is once it is
out of POC. [clarified: 60% POC threshold, 80-90% production target]

PARTICIPANT: KB layering is correct. [confirmed]

